  "prompt": "Does money laundering fall under criminal legislation?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is considered a criminal offense under both domestic and international law. Most countries have specific anti-money laundering (AML) legislation that criminalizes the process of disguising the origins of illegally obtained money. This typically involves:\n\n1. Transforming \"dirty\" money from criminal activities into seemingly \"clean\" funds\n2. Hiding the source of money to make it appear legitimate\n3. Penalties that can include substantial fines and imprisonment\n\nLegislation varies by jurisdiction, but money laundering is generally prosecuted under criminal codes and financial regulations.",
